As soon as walking into the restaurant for a late  lunch I was greeted by Marco. Speaking Italian with him confirmed that I was in a genuine Italian “ristorante” and not just another franchise, so, I accepted to be seated. The staff is literally international, which gave me an unique chance to speak also French, Romanian, and listening to Spanish, another delightful surprise that counter-set the mood for a lonely meal. Food was made from scratch and naturally, with very fresh ingredients, something that I immediately recognized since I grew up in Europe. The hand made “grissini” sprinkled with black sesame seeds, are definitely a “home run”. Not lastly, desert was delicious and not sweet - perfect for my choice. Parking is next door which is one less headache of dealing with traffic to hunt for a spot in the street.Judged only by pictures of the fooddoes not do justice to my entire experience here. Service was excellent but not stiff like that of 5-star restaurants. It had a relaxed attitude that reminded me with nostalgia of “la dolce vita” in Italy. Later in the day the restaurant was packed and it became so loud that I couldn’t hear my own thoughts. I still can’t forget that screechy voice and hyena laugh. Next time I’ll bring my ear plugs or better, try my best to avoid rush hour when in town.
